  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\nWhen besu is running as an execution client, the normal 'forward' sync process should stop at terminal-total-difficulty.  However, post-merge besu needs to do a 'backwards sync' and fetch blocks backward from a given block hash until we reach a common ancestor.\n\nSpecs are still a moving target on this but this behavior is specified :\n* https://github.com/fjl/p2p-drafts/blob/master/merge-sync/merge-sync.md#definitions\n* https://github.com/ethereum/execution-apis/blob/main/src/engine/interop/specification.md#engine_executepayload\n* https://notes.ethereum.org/@djrtwo/BJxKBaqNF\n\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n* forward sync until TTD\n* backward sync upon executePayload for an unknown header \n* conformance to final sync spec",
